			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2022</a> paper:</span><br><i>Yet Another Generating Method of Fluent Interfaces Supporting Flat- and Sub-chaining Styles</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/TetsuroYamazaki.html">Tetsuro Yamazaki</a>, <a href="../profile/TomokiNakamaru.html">Tomoki Nakamaru</a>, <a href="../profile/ShigeruChiba.html">Shigeru Chiba</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1145/3567512.3567533">10.1145/3567512.3567533</a></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4c.html"><span class="tagM">T4C: Vertical Transformation</span></a><ul><li> It presents a generative method to produce fluent interfaces with compile-time guarantees.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t3f.html"><span class="tagL">T3F: API</span></a><ul><li> Fluent interfaces are a form of API, and the paper targets their safe usage patterns.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t1b.html"><span class="tagL">T1B: Static Semantics</span></a><ul><li> Static checking of calling conventions relies on type-system/static-semantics mechanisms.
</li></ul></li></ul>
